Privacy Policy

This privacy policy ("Policy") explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect the information provided by users ("User" or "you") when using our Discord bot, "Meowy" ("Bot"). By using the Bot, you consent to the practices described in this Policy.

1. Information We Collect

1.1 Personal Information: We do not collect any personally identifiable information (PII), such as names, email addresses, or contact information, from users of the Bot.

1.2 Usage Data: We may collect anonymous usage data, such as bot commands executed, messages sent, and interactions with the Bot. This data is used solely for the purpose of improving the functionality, performance, and user experience of the Bot.

2. Use of Information

2.1 Anonymous Usage Data: The anonymous usage data we collect is used to analyze trends, track bot performance, identify and fix issues, and enhance the features and functionality of the Bot. We may also use this data to generate aggregated and anonymized statistics or reports.

2.2 Data Retention: We retain the anonymous usage data collected from the Bot for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Policy. We may also retain and use this data as necessary to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements.

2.3 Data Sharing: We do not sell, trade, or transfer any personal or usage data collected through the Bot to third parties. However, we may share aggregated and anonymized data with trusted third parties for research, analytics, and statistical purposes, provided that such data cannot be used to identify individual users.

2.4 Legal Compliance: We may disclose any information, including anonymous usage data, if required to do so by law or if we believe in good faith that such disclosure is necessary to comply with legal obligations, protect our rights, investigate fraud, or respond to government requests.

3. Data Security

3.1 Data Protection: We implement reasonable security measures to protect the data collected through the Bot, including encryption, access controls, and regular system updates. However, please be aware that no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of any data transmitted or stored using the Bot.

3.2 User Responsibilities: You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of any access credentials or personal information associated with your Discord account. We recommend using strong, unique passwords and enabling two-factor authentication to protect your account and data.

4. Third-Party Services

4.1 Links to Third-Party Websites: The Bot may contain links to third-party websites or services that are not owned or controlled by us. This Policy does not apply to those third-party websites or services. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of those third parties before providing any personal information or using their services.

4.2 Service Providers: We may engage trusted third-party service providers to assist us in operating, maintaining, and improving the Bot. These service providers will have access to the data collected through the Bot only to the extent necessary to perform their functions and are obligated to maintain the confidentiality and security of the data.

5. Children's Privacy

5.1 Compliance with Applicable Laws: The Bot is not directed to individuals under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we become aware that we have unintentionally collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to promptly delete the information from our records.

6. Changes to this Privacy Policy

6.1 Policy Updates: We reserve the right to update or modify this Policy at any time, and any changes will be effective upon posting the revised Policy on our website or notifying you through the Bot. We encourage you to review this Policy periodically to stay informed about how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information.

7. Your Rights and Choices

7.1 Data Access and Control: You have the right to access, correct, or delete the data collected through the Bot. If you would like to exercise any of these rights or have any questions about the data we collect, please contact us using the information provided in Section 8.

8. Contact Us

